ðŸŸ¦ 1. kubectl Basics

kubectl is how you interact with your Kubernetes cluster.

Check Cluster & Nodes
kubectl cluster-info
kubectl get nodes -o wide

Check System Pods
kubectl get pods -A

Deploy a Test App
kubectl create deployment nginx --image=nginx
kubectl get deployments
kubectl get pods

Expose the App as a Service
kubectl expose deployment nginx --port=80 --type=NodePort
kubectl get svc


Now you can access NGINX via http://<NodeIP>:<NodePort>.
